  "prompt": "Which countries have never been conquered, colonized, or ruled by any other country?",
  "response": "There are very few countries that have never been conquered, colonized, or ruled by another nation. Some notable examples include:\n\n1. Thailand (Siam) - The only Southeast Asian country never colonized by European powers.\n\n2. Japan - Although it was occupied by the United States after World War II, it was never fully colonized in the traditional sense.\n\n3. Ethiopia - Briefly occupied by Italy from 1936-1941, but successfully resisted long-term colonization.\n\n4. Iran (Persia) - Maintained independence throughout most of its history, though it was influenced by various empires.\n\n5. Nepal - Remained independent despite being between powerful empires like British India and China.\n\n6. Bhutan - Maintained independence and avoided direct colonization.\n\n7. Luxembourg - While occupied during wars, it was never fully colonized.\n\n8. San Marino - One of the world's oldest republics, never conquered.\n\n9. Vatican City - Technically an independent state that has never been colonized.\n\nIt's worth noting that the definition of \"colonization\" can be complex, and many countries have experienced some form of external control or significant foreign influence throughout history. The list above represents countries that have maintained substantial independence.",
